Context:
Four plugins read meta tags for auth detection:
- GitHub: `document.querySelector<HTMLMetaElement>('meta[name="user-login"]')?.content`
- Jira: `document.querySelector('meta[name="ajs-atlassian-account-id"]')?.getAttribute('content')`
- Confluence: has a local `getMetaContent` helper: `const getMetaContent = (name: string): string | null => document.querySelector(\`meta[name="${name}"]\`)?.getAttribute('content') ?? null;`
- GitLab: `document.querySelector<HTMLMetaElement>('meta[name="csrf-token"]')?.content`

Changes:
Add to dom.ts after getTextContent (after line 248):
```typescript
export const getMetaContent = (name: string): string | null => {
  if (!name) return null;
  try {
    const meta = document.querySelector<HTMLMetaElement>(`meta[name="${CSS.escape(name)}"]`);
    return meta?.content ?? null;
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
};
```

Use `CSS.escape(name)` to prevent CSS injection in the selector. This is defensive — meta names are typically alphanumeric, but an unsafe name could break the querySelector.

Add to index.ts DOM exports (line 174):
```typescript
export { getMetaContent, getTextContent, observeDOM, querySelectorAll, waitForSelector, waitForSelectorRemoval } from './dom.js';
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change any existing DOM functions
- Use CSS.escape for the name parameter in the selector
- Return null (not empty string) when meta tag is missing or has no content

