Context:
Two plugins need to search localStorage by key pattern:

Teams (plugins/teams/src/teams-api.ts:27-45) searches for MSAL tokens:
```typescript
for (let i = 0; i < localStorage.length; i++) {
  const key = localStorage.key(i);
  if (!key) continue;
  if (key.includes('login.windows.net') && key.includes('accesstoken')) {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem(key);
    // ...
  }
}
```

ClickHouse (plugins/clickhouse/src/clickhouse-api.ts:26-42) searches for Auth0 tokens:
```typescript
const raw = localStorage.getItem(AUTH0_STORAGE_KEY); // but also searches @@auth0spajs@@:: prefix keys
```

The SDK's getLocalStorage(key) only reads a specific key by name.

Changes:
Add to storage.ts after getLocalStorage (after the closing of the iframe fallback at line 52):
```typescript
export const findLocalStorageEntry = (
  predicate: (key: string) => boolean,
): { key: string; value: string } | null => {
  const search = (storage: Storage): { key: string; value: string } | null => {
    for (let i = 0; i < storage.length; i++) {
      const key = storage.key(i);
      if (key !== null && predicate(key)) {
        const value = storage.getItem(key);
        if (value !== null) return { key, value };
      }
    }
    return null;
  };

  try {
    return search(localStorage);
  } catch {
    // Direct access failed
  }

  // Same iframe fallback as getLocalStorage
  let storage: Storage | undefined;
  try {
    storage = localStorage as Storage | undefined;
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
  if (storage !== undefined) return null;

  try {
    const iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
    iframe.style.display = 'none';
    document.body.appendChild(iframe);
    try {
      const iframeStorage = iframe.contentWindow?.localStorage;
      return iframeStorage ? search(iframeStorage) : null;
    } finally {
      document.body.removeChild(iframe);
    }
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
};
```

Add to index.ts Storage exports section (around line 215).

Constraints:
- Do NOT change getLocalStorage or any existing function
- Must use the same iframe fallback pattern as getLocalStorage (for Discord-like environments)
- The predicate receives only the key, not the value (avoid reading all values upfront)
- Returns the FIRST matching entry, not all matches (plugins only need one token)
